# UI/UX Patterns & Guidelines

General UI/UX patterns and best practices for building consistent, accessible user interfaces.

## Component Patterns

### Cards

#### Standard Card
```tsx
<div className="bg-card border border-border rounded-[20px] p-6">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

#### Card with Shadow
```tsx
<div className="bg-card border border-border rounded-[20px] p-6 shadow-soft">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

#### Card with Hover
```tsx
<div className="bg-card border border-border rounded-[20px] p-6 hover:shadow-soft transition-shadow">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

### Icon Badges

Standard pattern for icon containers:
```tsx
<div className="icon-badge p-4 rounded-[16px]">
  <Icon className="h-6 w-6 text-primary-foreground" />
</div>
```

Variations:
- `p-3` for smaller badges
- `p-4` for standard (most common)
- `p-6` for larger badges

### Button Variants

- **Default**: Primary color, solid
- **Outline**: Border, transparent background
- **Ghost**: No border, transparent background
- **Locked**: Disabled state styling
- **Destructive**: Red/destructive color for delete actions

### Form Patterns

#### Input Field
```tsx
<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="field">Label</Label>
  <Input
    id="field"
    className="bg-background border-border rounded-[12px]"
    placeholder="Placeholder"
  />
</div>
```

#### Textarea
```tsx
<Textarea
  className="min-h-[100px] bg-background border-border resize-none"
  placeholder="Placeholder"
/>
```

### Empty States

Consistent pattern across pages:
```tsx
<EmptyState
  icon={Icon}
  title="Title"
  description="Description"
  actionLabel="Action" // optional
  onAction={handler} // optional
/>
```

Styling: Card with centered content, icon badge, title, description, optional action button.

