## Spacing System

### Container Spacing

- **Standard Pages**: `p-6 space-y-6`
- **Reduced Padding Pages**: `p-4 space-y-6` (for content-dense pages)
- **Hero Pages**: `px-4 pt-6 pb-6` (for full-width hero sections)

### Max Widths

- **Standard Content**: `max-w-2xl` (most pages, forms)
- **Wide Content**: `max-w-4xl` (detail pages, galleries)
- **Full Width**: `max-w-7xl` (admin dashboards, data tables)

### Card Spacing

- **Card Padding**: `p-6` (standard)
- **Card Content**: `space-y-4` (internal spacing)
- **Section Spacing**: `space-y-6` (between major sections)

### Grid Spacing

- **Standard Grid**: `gap-4` (2 columns)
- **Responsive Grid**: `gap-4` (2→3→4 columns responsive)
- **Horizontal Scroll**: `gap-4` with `px-2` or `px-4` container padding

### Button Spacing

- **Button Groups**: `gap-3` or `flex-1` for side-by-side
- **Icon + Text**: `mr-2` for icon margin
- **Full Width**: `w-full` with `rounded-[12px]` or `rounded-full`

## Typography

### Headings

- **Page Title (Large)**: `text-5xl font-bold` (main page titles)
- **Page Title (Smaller)**: `text-4xl font-bold` (secondary pages)
- **Section Heading**: `text-2xl font-bold` (major sections)
- **Subsection Heading**: `text-lg font-semibold` (subsections)
- **Card Title**: `text-xl font-bold` (action cards, item cards)

### Body Text

- **Large Description**: `text-lg text-muted-foreground` (page descriptions)
- **Standard**: `text-sm` or `text-base` (descriptions, content)
- **Muted**: `text-muted-foreground` (secondary text)
- **Small**: `text-xs` (badges, metadata)

### Leading/Tracking

- **Tight**: `leading-tight` (headings)
- **Relaxed**: `leading-relaxed` (body paragraphs)
- **Normal**: Default (most text)

### Font Weights

- **Bold**: `font-bold` (headings, titles)
- **Semibold**: `font-semibold` (subsection headings)
- **Medium**: `font-medium` (labels, emphasis)
- **Normal**: Default (body text)

## Colors & Theming

### Color Tokens

- **Primary**: Main brand color (buttons, active states, icons)
- **Foreground**: Primary text color
- **Muted Foreground**: Secondary text (`text-muted-foreground`)
- **Background**: Page background
- **Card**: Card background (`bg-card`)
- **Border**: Border color (`border-border`)
- **Destructive**: Error/destructive actions

### Shadow System

- **Shadow Soft**: `shadow-soft` utility (cards, hover states)
- **Shadow Gold**: `shadow-gold` utility (special emphasis, if available)
- **Default**: Tailwind shadows for elevated elements

## Common Layout Patterns

### Horizontal Scroll Sections

Pattern for scrollable horizontal lists:
```tsx
<div className="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 px-4 pb-2">
  <div className="flex gap-4 min-w-max">
    {/* Cards */}
  </div>
</div>
```

Uses negative margin (`-mx-4`) to extend to edges, then positive padding (`px-4`) to maintain internal spacing.

### Fixed Bottom Actions

Pattern for sticky bottom buttons:
```tsx
<div className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 bg-card border-t border-border p-4 z-10">
  <div className="max-w-2xl mx-auto w-full">
    <Button className="w-full">Action</Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

Content padding: `pb-24` to prevent overlap with fixed bottom element.

### Hero Banner Overlay

Standard pattern for hero sections:
```tsx
<div className="relative">
  <AspectRatio ratio={16 / 9}>
    <img src={url} className="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" />
    <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-background to-transparent" />
  </AspectRatio>
  <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 px-4 pb-6">
    {/* Overlay content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

## Responsive Breakpoints

- **sm**: 640px+ (grid: 3 columns, increased spacing)
- **md**: 768px+ (grid: 4 columns, larger text sizes)
- **lg**: 1024px+ (future breakpoint usage)
- **xl**: 1280px+ (future breakpoint usage)

## Accessibility

### ARIA Labels

- All interactive elements have `aria-label` or `ariaLabel` props
- Buttons have descriptive labels
- Navigation items have labels
- Form inputs are properly labeled with `htmlFor` associations

### Focus States

Standard focus visible pattern:
```tsx
className="focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
```

Used on interactive cards and buttons for keyboard navigation visibility.

### Reduced Motion Support

**Always implement**: Every animated component MUST respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

#### Tailwind Animations
Tailwind animations automatically respect `prefers-reduced-motion` via CSS media queries when properly configured.

#### Custom Animations
For custom animations not using Tailwind utilities, always check for reduced motion preference:

```tsx
const [prefersReducedMotion, setPrefersReducedMotion] = React.useState(false);

React.useEffect(() => {
  const mediaQuery = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)');
  setPrefersReducedMotion(mediaQuery.matches);
  
  const handleChange = (e: MediaQueryListEvent) => {
    setPrefersReducedMotion(e.matches);
  };
  
  mediaQuery.addEventListener('change', handleChange);
  return () => mediaQuery.removeEventListener('change', handleChange);
}, []);

// Disable animations if preferred
const effectiveTransition = prefersReducedMotion
  ? { duration: 0 }
  : { duration: 0.2, ease: [0.4, 0, 0.2, 1] };
```

#### Static Content
Most headings and static content should render immediately without animation. Reserve animations for:
- User-triggered interactions (button clicks, hover states)
- List/grid items appearing (stagger fade)
- State transitions that provide feedback

Avoid animating static page headings and static text content.

### Semantic HTML

- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Semantic navigation elements (`nav`, `header`, `footer`)
- Button elements for interactive actions (not divs styled as buttons)
- Form elements properly structured with labels

## Border Radius

Consistent border radius values:
- **Standard**: `rounded-[12px]` (inputs, buttons)
- **Medium**: `rounded-[16px]` (icon badges, small cards)
- **Large**: `rounded-[20px]` (cards, containers)
- **Full**: `rounded-full` (circular elements, pills)

## Icon Sizes

Consistent icon size patterns:
- **Small**: `h-4 w-4` (inline text icons, badges)
- **Medium**: `h-5 w-5` (default buttons, navigation)
- **Large**: `h-6 w-6` (card icons, hero icons)
- **XLarge**: `h-8 w-8` (feature icons, section headers)

## Animation Guidelines

See `.cursor/rules/code/uiux/animations.mdc` for comprehensive animation guidelines including:
- Timing standards (120-240ms for UI feedback)
- Standard easing curve (`cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`)
- Scale limits (2% max for hover/tap)
- Reduced motion support
- Performance requirements
